Base.Explanation: Check if a session maintained by the Powershell Agent service still exists. The session is requied for a number of UMRA script actions that use the Powershell Agent service. See the online help for more information.

ArrayElement.Name: Session ID
ArrayElement.Description: The identifier of the Powershell Agent service session that must be checked. The value is generated with previously executed action 'Setup Powershell Agent service session'.

ArrayElement.Name: Session flag
ArrayElement.Description: An output property that indicates if the specified session exists. The returned value of the flag is either 'Yes' or 'No'.

Base.Name: @VO Connection
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the PowerShell Agent service session.

Base.Name: Webservice location
Base.Description: The location of the @VO hosted environment. For example 'https://nnnn.atvo.nl/services/cxf/umraService?wsdl'

Base.Name: Brin number
Base.Description: The brin number of the school.

Base.Name: Login name
Base.Description: The name of the user to use to login to the hosted @VO environment.

Base.Name: Password
Base.Description: The password of the user to use to login to the hosted @VO environment. The value specified here, must be an encrypted variable. Use the action 'Set encrypted variable' or 'Encrypt text' to create such a variable. The value specified here will not be shown in the UMRA logs and will be sent encrypted to the UMRA PowerShell agent.

Base.Name: Time out
Base.Description: The number of seconds before an action will time out. If not specified the incremental pattern is activated. (recommended.)

Base.Name: Proxy server
Base.Description: The address of the proxy server. For example: 'http://proxy'.

Base.Name: Proxy port
Base.Description: The port of the proxy server. For example: 3128.

Base.Name: Proxy login name
Base.Description: The name of the user to use to login to the proxy server.

Base.Name: Proxy Password
Base.Description: The password of the user to use to login to the proxy server. The value specified here, must be an encrypted variable. Use the action 'Set encrypted variable' or 'Encrypt text' to create such a variable. The value specified here will not be shown in the UMRA logs and will be sent encrypted to the UMRA PowerShell agent.

Base.Name: Advanced: Logging mask
Base.Description: The mask specified here, determines the logging output of ALL the PowerShell actions in this session. Default all messages except debug messages are shown. The mask is build from the following numbers: 1 = Normal, 2 = Error, 4 = Warning, 8 = Info, 128 = Debug. If not specified the number 7 is used.

Base.Explanation: Retrieves all the students in the @VO environment.

Base.Name: @VO Connection
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the PowerShell Agent service session.

Base.Name: Year Level
Base.Description: The number of historical school years, to retrieve inactive students for. If not specified the value is 1. Therefore the active and non-active students of this school year and inactive students of the previous school year are retrieved.

Base.Name: Active Students
Base.Description: The active students in the @VO environment. This produces a table with the following 40 columns: 'StudentId', 'BSN', 'StudentCode', 'UserName', 'Initials', 'FirstName', 'Middlename', 'LastName', 'Gender', 'BirthDate', 'Address', 'Street', 'StreetNumber', 'StreetNumberSuffix', 'PostalCode', 'City', 'HomeTelephoneNumber', 'HomeTelephoneNumberIsSecret', 'MobileNumber', 'SchoolYear', 'Class', 'EducationName', 'EducationCode', 'ProfileSector', 'LocationName', 'LocationCode', 'LocationNumber', 'Courses', 'Mentors', 'EducationalPeriod', 'Clusters', 'Active', 'ActiveText', 'AccessPassNumber', 'OpendId', 'ExternExportId', 'CostBrinName', 'CostBrinNumber', 'EMail' and 'VaultUsage'.

Base.Name: Non-Active Students
Base.Description: The in active students in the @VO environment. This produces a table with the following 40 columns: 'StudentId', 'BSN', 'StudentCode', 'UserName', 'Initials', 'FirstName', 'Middlename', 'LastName', 'Gender', 'BirthDate', 'Address', 'Street', 'StreetNumber', 'StreetNumberSuffix', 'PostalCode', 'City', 'HomeTelephoneNumber', 'HomeTelephoneNumberIsSecret', 'MobileNumber', 'SchoolYear', 'Class', 'EducationName', 'EducationCode', 'ProfileSector', 'LocationName', 'LocationCode', 'LocationNumber', 'Courses', 'Mentors', 'EducationalPeriod', 'Clusters', 'Active', 'ActiveText', 'OpendId', 'ExternExportId', 'CostBrinName', 'CostBrinNumber', 'EMail' and 'VaultUsage'.

Base.Explanation: Retrieves all the caregivers in the @VO environment.

Base.Name: @VO Connection
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the PowerShell Agent service session.

Base.Name: Filter: Caregiver type
Base.Description: A comma separated value, specifying the types of caregivers to return. For example, 'father, mother'. If not specified there will not be filtered on the type of caregiver.

Base.Name: Filter: Legal representative
Base.Description: Set to 'Yes' to return only care givers who are a legal representative of a student. Set to 'No' to return only caregivers who are not a legal representative of a student. If not specified, both, non legal representatives and legal representatives are returned.

Base.Name: Caregivers
Base.Description: The caregivers in the @VO environment. This produces a table with the following 29 columns: 'CaregiverId', 'BSN', 'UserName', 'Initials', 'MiddleName', 'LastName', 'Gender', 'Address', 'Street', 'StreetHouseNumber', 'StreetSuffix', 'PostalCode', 'City', 'BillingAddress', 'BillingAddressText', 'HomePhoneNumber', 'HomePhoneNumberIsSecret', 'MobileNumber', 'MobileNumberIsSecret', 'WorkMobileNumber', 'WorkMobileNumberIsSecret', 'CaregiverType', 'BankAccount', 'LegalRepresentative', 'LegalRepresentativeText', 'EMail', 'OpendId', 'PostAddress' and 'ExternExportId'.

Base.Name: Caregiver students
Base.Description: The caregiver - student relation in the @VO environment. This produces a table with the following 12 columns: 'CaregiverId', 'StudentId', 'StudentBSN', 'EducationalID', 'CaregiverType', 'BillingAddress', 'BillingAddressText', 'LegalRepresentative', 'LegalRepresentativeText', 'PostAddress', 'PostAddressText' and 'ExternExportId'.
